Privacy Policy and Terms of Service
MoreMins Privacy Policy
This is an updated
MoreMins
Privacy Policy. It is set in accordance to the new standards introduced by the European data protection law known as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) which came into effect on 25 May 2018.
For existing MoreMins users: nothing is changing about your current settings or how your information is processed.
This Privacy Policy (together with our Terms & Conditions and any other documents referred to in it) sets out the basis on which any personal data we collect from you, or that you provide to us in connection with our website www.moremins.com (“Website”),
MoreMins
mobile application (“App”) all of the foregoing, collectively, the Services. Please read the following carefully to understand our views and practices regarding your personal data and how we will treat it.
For the purpose of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (EU), the data controller and processor is Moremins Ltd, 71-75 Shelton Street, London, WC2H 9JQ ("
MoreMins
", "us", "our", "we" or “Services”, “Service”).
By accessing and/or using our Services you consent to us collecting, processing, storing and sharing information about you in the manners set out in this Policy. By downloading the App and/or using the Services you acknowledge you are of legal age.
1. DOWNLOADING AND REGISTERING IN MOREMINS APP OR STARTING USING THE SERVICES
By joining
MoreMins
you acknowledge that you understand and agree to our Privacy Policy and Terms & Conditions, provide true and accurate information and are fully authorized to sign an agreement for the Services.  If you join or register to
MoreMins
, it means that you sign an agreement for the Services.
By registering in App you give your consent for us to collect, use and store the following information:
1.  Phone number with a country code
2.  Email
3.  Your device information, OS, app version
- How we use your personal information
1.  Using your phone number:
To send SMS with an access code for a phone number verification.
To identify you as the user of our Services.
To contact you regarding your account.
In some rare cases to contact you about our special offers.
To provide country-specific information regarding Services updates or peculiarities.
To prevent, detect, mitigate, and investigate fraud, security breaches or other potentially prohibited or illegal activities.
2.  Using your email:
To send your account login details.
To send your account balance information.
To send general information how to use Services.
To inform you about Service updates.
For marketing and advertising of our Service or our Service partners.
To measure a performance of our email marketing campaigns (e.g. by analyzing open and click rates).
3.
Using your
device information, OS, app version:
This information is used to troubleshoot problems in the event of a fault.
2. ADDITIONAL OPTIONAL INFORMATION
After installing
MoreMins
App you will be allowed to import your contact book into
MoreMins
App. We will not collect, store or transfer your contact book details. You will be able to use your imported contact book for calling via
MoreMins
App in the most convenient way.
You have an option to share some additional personal details with us when you log into the self-service system of the Website.
Additional Personal Details:
1. Name, Surname
2. Your address
- How we use your additional personal information
1.  Using your name, surname:
To address you by the name when needed.
2.  Using your address:
To provide you with location-based information regarding Services or our Services partners.
3. BUYING BUNDLE OR TOPPING-UP VIA WEBSITE OR APP
Payments for the Service are processed by secured and licensed payment processors (third-parties).
By making any card payment within the App or on our Website you will be asked to provide your credit/debit card information or PayPal account details for the payment provider to process the transaction.
MoreMins
does not store your credit/debit card information, PayPal account details or bank account passwords.
MoreMins
Website communicates with payment processor websites over Secure Socket Layer protocol (SSL) to ensure protection of your personal data.
Please note that payment processors are not under the control of
MoreMins
.
4. MAKING A CALL
MoreMins
does not record your conversations.
MoreMins
system automatically documents time and duration of a call, completion status, source number and destination number, billing information (price of a call) in Call Detail Record (CDR).
CDR is needed for billing purposes, for improving the Service, for fulfilling our obligations under applicable laws.
5. YOUR CHOICES ABOUT YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
- Marketing and Newsletters via email
If you do not wish to receive emails from us, you can unsubscribe via the link in an email you received.
Keep in mind, we do not sell or disclose your personal information to third-parties for their marketing purposes without your consent.
- Your name, surname, address and email
Login to your account on our website www.moremins.com to change or delete your name, surname, address and email.
- Your account status
If you do not wish to get emails with your balance notifications or expiration dates of bundles, send us an email to info@moremins.com.
- Your phone number
If you wish to change your phone number, send us an email to info@moremins.com.
There is no way to use the Service without giving us your phone number.
- Promotional SMS
You can unsubscribe to promotional SMS by sending us an email to info@moremins.com.
- Deleting your account
Send us an email with your phone number to info@moremins.com if you want to permanently delete your
MoreMins
account.
- A copy of your personal information
You have the right to know what personal information we maintain about you.
We will provide you with a copy of your personal information in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format on request.
- Procession of your request
Please include your full name, phone number and email address associated with your account, and a detailed description of your data request. Such requests will be processed in line with local laws. We will respond to any requests for access to personal information within 30 days.
6. SHARING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION WITH THIRD-PARTIES
- Provision of Services
We will not disclose your personal information to third-parties, except when it is necessary for us to provide the Services for you.
We may hire other companies to provide the Services on our behalf, such as:
providing customer support;
hosting Website;
hosting App;
providing technical support;
advertising;
providing call transit, etc.
Those companies would be permitted to obtain only the personal information they need to deliver the Services, not more. They would be prohibited from using this information for any other purpose.
- User Testimonials
We display personal testimonials of satisfied customers on our site in addition to other endorsements. With your consent we may post your testimonial along with your name. If you wish to update or delete your testimonial, you can contact us at info@moremins.com.
- Social Media Widgets
Our Website includes social media features, such as the Facebook Like button and widgets, such as the ‘Share This’ button or interactive mini-programs that run on our site. These features may collect your IP address, which page you are visiting on our site, and may set a cookie to enable the feature to function properly. Social media features and widgets are either hosted by a third-party or hosted directly on our web site. Your interactions with these features are governed by the privacy policy of the company providing it.
- Data analysis services
We use Google Analytics or equivalent service in both the Website and the App to improve the Service and to analyze statistics.
- Disclosures to Protect Us or Others (e.g., as Required by Law and Similar Disclosures).
We may access, preserve, and disclose your Personal Information, other Account information, and content if we believe doing so is required or appropriate to: (i) comply with law enforcement or national security requests and legal process, such as a court order or subpoena; (ii) respond to your requests; (iii) protect yours’, ours’ or others’ rights, property, or safety; (iv) to enforce our policies or contracts; (v) to collect amounts owed to
MoreMins
; (vi) when we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to prevent physical harm or financial loss or in connection with an investigation or prosecution of suspected or actual illegal activity; or (vii) if we, in good faith, believe that disclosure is otherwise necessary or advisable.
- Advertising
We do not sell or disclose your personal information to third-parties for their marketing and advertising purposes without your consent.
7. PERSONAL INFORMATION STORAGE  AND PROTECTION
- Information collection, storage
By using
MoreMins
Services you consent to storage of such information outside your country in
MoreMins
servers in the European Union.
- Children’s Personal Information
The Service and Website are not intended for, nor does
MoreMins
knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 16.
- Protection of Information
The security of your personal information is very important to us.
MoreMins
maintains reasonable security measures to protect your information from loss, destruction, misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure. When you enter sensitive information, such as a credit card details, on our order forms and login credentials on our website login page, we encrypt the transmission of that information using secure socket layer technology (SSL). These technologies help ensure that your data is safe, secure, and only available to you and to those you provided authorized access.
However, no data transmission over the Internet or information storage technology can be guaranteed to be 100% secure due to the nature of the distributed network that is the Internet. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
Our administrative security measures include physical, electronic and procedural safeguards.
- Our legal obligations
Under legal obligations we store a summary copy of your bills for six years from the date of the bill.
We store your contact details on file while you’re one of our customers, and for six years after; and details relating to any dispute for six years after it was closed.
In other cases we’ll store personal information for the periods needed for the purposes for which the information was collected or for which it is to be further processed. And sometimes we’ll keep it for longer if we need to by law. Otherwise we delete it.
8. THIRD-PARTY PRIVACY POLICIES
This privacy notice addresses only our use and handling of personal information we collect from you in connection with providing you our Service.
If you disclose your information to a third party, or visit a third party website via a link from our Services, their privacy notices and practices will apply to any personal information you provide to them or they collect from you.
9. CHANGES TO PRIVACY POLICY
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. You can review the most current version of this privacy policy at any time at https://www.moremins.com/en/terms-privacy/. Your continued use of the Website or Service constitutes your agreement to be bound by such changes to the privacy policy. Your only remedy, if you do not accept the terms of this privacy policy, is to discontinue use of the Site and Service. If we make any material changes we will notify you by email sent to the e-mail address on your account or by means of a notice on the Website prior to the change becoming effective.
10. COOKIES AND TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES
We, as well as third parties that provide content, analytics, advertising, or other functionality on our Services, may use cookies, pixel tags, local storage, and other technologies (“Technologies”) to automatically collect information through the Services.
You may stop or restrict the placement of cookies on your computer or smartphone or remove them from your browser by adjusting your web browser preferences. Please note that cookie-based opt-outs are not effective on mobile applications.
- Cookies
Cookies are small text files placed in visitors’ computer or smartphone browsers. These technologies are used in analyzing trends, administering the Website, tracking users’ movements around the Website and to gather demographic information about our user base as a whole. We may receive reports based on the use of these technologies by these companies on an individual as well as aggregated basis. Users can control the use of cookies at the individual browser level. If you reject cookies, you may still use our Website, but your ability to use some features or areas of our site may be limited.
- Pixel Tags/Web Beacons
A pixel tag (also known as a web beacon) is a piece of code embedded on the Website that collects information about users’ engagement on that web page. Pixel tags allow us to record, for example, that a user has visited a particular web page or clicked on a particular advertisement.
- Local Storage
We use Local Storage (LS) such as HTML5 to store content information and preferences. Various browsers may offer their own management tools for removing HTML5 LS.
11. DATA CONTROLLERS AND DATA PROTECTION OFFICERS
