MoreMins Terms & Conditions
PLEASE READ THESE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF SERVICE BEFORE USING THIS WEBSITE OR APP.
MoreMins
converts your local minutes into cheap international ones.
MoreMins
is a pay as you go, low cost international calling service. It is very convenient to use
MoreMins
Services with
MoreMins
App that is developed for smartphones with Android and iOS operating systems. There are absolutely no hidden fees or charges other than stated in the Website or your Account.
You can use
MoreMins
Services if you have an active mobile number (a mobile phone number and an active subscription at one of the mobile network operators in a country supported by
MoreMins
). Countries supported by
MoreMins
are listed in
MoreMins
App registration page and in the section of Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) on the Website.
MoreMins
converts your mobile network operator’s local minutes into cheap international ones. The Service is cheapest for those customers who get free minutes for local calls (to landline and mobile numbers) from their mobile network operator.
Register for
MoreMins
Services with a local SIM card (local phone number) issued by the country you are in. You should use your home network for calling abroad with
MoreMins
.
While making an international call with
MoreMins
you will:
1. automatically call to the local access number;
2. if
MoreMins
credit balance is sufficient, you will be connected with the person you are calling.
Cost of a call abroad with MoreMins =
price you pay your mobile network operator for local call (usually 0 p/min because you use inclusive minutes) + price you pay
MoreMins
(from 1.5 p/min) for international call.
1) Price you pay your mobile network operator per local call.
When you call abroad with
MoreMins
, you use your operator’s local minutes. In most cases, these minutes are free and included into your bundle or plan.
If you do not have any inclusive minutes left this month or have not got any inclusive minutes at all, then you pay to your mobile operator for a local call even if you are calling abroad.
In rare cases a call to local access number may be charged additionally as a local call according to your mobile network operator’s rate plan.
MoreMins advise you to check with your mobile network operator if a call to MoreMins local access number will be included into your inclusive free minutes. MoreMins also advise you to check whether you have any inclusive minutes left for local calls before making an international call with MoreMins.
2) Price you pay MoreMins for international call.
In addition to a local call price,
MoreMins
charges you for cheap international minutes. Or to put it another way, for a small fee
MoreMins
app converts your operator’s local minutes into international ones.
The person you are calling with
MoreMins
sees your usual mobile phone number.
